net.uniform.api

Interface ElementWithValueConversion<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type to convert values
    All Superinterfaces:
    Element
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Checkbox, DatePicker

    public interface ElementWithValueConversion<T>
extends Element
    This interface extends an Element features so it's able to override the conversion of its String values to any target type with any custom logic. This is used in the form getFormDataConvertedToElementValueTypes method.
    Author:
    Eduardo Ramos
    See Also:
    Element

      • getConvertedValue

        T getConvertedValue()
        Returns the final value for the list of values hold by the element. This is used for example by DatePicker element to return date objects instead of Strings.
        Returns:
        Value with the type declared by the element
